<subsection xml:id="subsec-Solving-angles-of-polygons">
    <title>Solving angles of polygons</title>

        <example>
        <statement>
            
            <p>
                Find the sum of interior angles of this polygon
            </p>

            <image width="50%">
                <shortdescription>Complex polygon</shortdescription>
                <latex-image>
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                        \draw[thick,purple] (0,0)--(2,2)--(1,2)--(1.5,3)--(-1,3)--(-2,2)--(0,0);
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
            </image>   
                
        </statement>

            
            <solution>
                <p>
                   The polygon has <m>6</m> sides.
                    Since all the sides are not equal, this is an irregular hexagon.
                </p>
                <p>
                   To work out the number of triangles in the hexagon, we subtract <m>2</m> from the number of sides of the hexagon  
                </p>
                <p>
                    <me>6 - 2 = 4</me>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Therefore, the sum of its interior angles can be found by <m>4 \times 180^\circ = 720^\circ</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    The sum of interior angles in a hexagon is <m>720^\circ</m>
                </p>
            </solution>
                
            
        </example>

        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    A regular polygon has six sides.determine:
                </p>
                <tabular>
                    <row>
                        <cell>(a) The size of each interior angle </cell>
                        <cell> (b) The size of each exterior angle.</cell>
                    </row>
                </tabular>
                
            </statement>
         <solution>
            <p>
                (a) sum of interior angles is <me>
                    (2n-4)\times 90^\circ=(2 \times 6-4)\times 90^\circ  </me>   
            </p>

            <p>
                <me>=(12-4)\times 90^\circ    </me>
           </p>

           <p>
                <me>
                   = 8 \times 90^\circ
                </me>
           </p>

           <p>
                <me>
                 =720^\circ   
                </me>  
           </p>

           <p>
            size of each interior angle <me>
               = \frac{720^\circ}{6}  </me> 
           </p>

           <p>
                <me>
                   = 120^\circ
                </me>
          </p>

          <p>
            (b).Size of each exterior angle is <me>
               = \frac{360^\circ}{n}=\frac{360}{6}
            </me> 
          </p>

          <p>
                <me>
                   = 60^\circ
                </me>
            
          </p>

         </solution>
        </example>


        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    The sum of the interior angles of a regular polygon is <m>540^\circ.</m> Deterimine the number of sides of the polygon.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <m>(2n-4) \times 90^\circ = 540^\circ</m>
                </p>

                <p>
                    <m>180n-360^\circ=540^\circ</m>
                </p>

                <p>
                    <m>180n-360^\circ+360^\circ=540^\circ+360^\circ</m>
                </p>

                <p>
                    <me>180n=900^\circ</me>
                </p>

                <p>
                    <me>n=5</me>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>

</subsection>
